					<span class="printuser avatarhover"><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/psul" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(2156983); return false;"  ><img class="small" src="http://www.wikidot.com/avatar.php?userid=2156983&amp;amp;size=small&amp;amp;timestamp=1610226556" alt="psul" style="background-image:url(http://www.wikidot.com/userkarma.php?u=2156983)"/></a><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/psul" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(2156983); return false;" >psul</a></span> <span class="odate time_1504415816 format_%25e%20%25b%20%25Y%2C%20%25H%3A%25M%7Cagohover">03 Sep 2017 05:16</span>
														</div>
			</div>
			<div class="content" id="post-content-3584144">
									

<p>Perhaps I'm wrong, but SCP-2696 always struck me as a story you were particularly invested in, minmin. This has that same feeling, to great effect. The wonderfully shaded characters, gripping action sequence and themes of family and acceptance of death - all of it is extremely high quality and enjoyable.</p>

							</div>

								
					
