															</div>
				<div class="info">
					<span class="printuser avatarhover"><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/minmin" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(560062); return false;"  ><img class="small" src="http://www.wikidot.com/avatar.php?userid=560062&amp;amp;size=small&amp;amp;timestamp=1610226556" alt="minmin" style="background-image:url(http://www.wikidot.com/userkarma.php?u=560062)"/></a><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/minmin" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(560062); return false;" >minmin</a></span> <span class="odate time_1504428993 format_%25e%20%25b%20%25Y%2C%20%25H%3A%25M%7Cagohover">03 Sep 2017 08:56</span>
														</div>
			</div>
			<div class="content" id="post-content-3584221">
									

<p>Yep&#8230; I just really love the dynamic against the unknown I've set up here - it's the Foundation's &quot;if not us, then who?&quot; die-in-the-dark mentality distilled into a set of clear rules and players and monsters in my head - like Mol narrates, there's a certain romanticism there, but there's also the romanticism that it's <em>my</em> rules and players and monsters, y'know?</p>
<p>Plus a good amount of it was brainstormed and written while I was doing an actual public security stint at [LOCATION REDACTED] irl, as part of my conscription with the Singapore army. So there's a lot of real-life intersect going on here too, and a fair bit of wishful glorification of what was ultimately a very mundane deployment.</p>
<p>And a lot of the personal things here are kind of drawn from my own, too. I feel like I've changed a lot in the past year from when I started writing this - in a freezing, yellow-lit concrete-walled bunker with frosted windows, bunk beds stacked to the ceiling and less than a feet apart - to now - starting out college, making new friends, learning new things, finding a personal level for myself - and finishing this and uploading it kind of means something to me, in putting all of that out in words and magitech ghost-killing. In a way it's the first time I'm kind of using characters as a way to act out my feelings about life and things in general, which I believe does contribute to what a lot of readers find as &quot;real&quot; and &quot;emotionally deep&quot;. Hey, if it works, it works.</p>

							</div>

								
