														</div>
			</div>
			<div class="content" id="post-content-3878050">
									

<p>Making a new comment here to draw some attention to this article, because it deserves more readers.</p>
<p>It's long - feels almost like a novella - but there's no filler. The prose is rich enough to make for a good read in itself, but the action and the way the characters interact with the supernatural keep things exciting all the way through, and the character development more than justifies the length. To top it off, this hints at an original interpretation of what life in the SCPF is like; there's enough worldbuilding in this that it would be interesting to readers totally unfamiliar with the setting.</p>

							</div>

								
					
